Products.FullDescription: Streets Golden Gaytime Unicorn Limited Edition
Products.RichDescription:
STREETS GOLDEN GAYTIME ICE CREAM UNICORN 400 ML

SAY GOODBYE SERIOUS, HELLO JOY. Introducing the Gaytime Unicorn. There's nothing else like it – it’s your favourite Gaytime ice cream with magical pink crumbs! A unique combination of smooth blue and pink creamy ice cream and delicious pink Gaytime crumbs, it really is hard to have a Gaytime on your own! Grab a box to share with your family and friends. Between WWI and WWII, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one-horse- power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well known brands such as Magnum, Paddle Pop and Blue Ribbon. Gaytime can be traced back to 1959 when it was first released to the Australian public. Since then, it has become an Australian icon, with the birth of the Golden Gaytime that we all know and love in 1970!

Gaytime Flavoured Ice Cream

Covered with magical pink crumbs!

Your favourite Gaytime

With a Unicorn Twist

Limited Edition Crumb Range

4 delicious chances to have a gaytime!

Products.SmallFormatDescription: Weis Mango & Toasted Coconut Frozen Yoghurt
Products.FullDescription: Weis Mango & Toasted Coconut Frozen Yoghurt
Products.RichDescription:
WEIS FROZEN YOGHURT MANGO COCONUT 1 LTR
There's nothing quite like real Aussie mangoes ripened in the sun and hand sorted for that unbeatable taste of sunshine. We blend them with delicious creamy yoghurt and toasted coconut to give you an authentic and tasty treat with only 11.3g of sugar per serve - and it's gluten free! Founded in Toowoomba, Queensland in 1957 with the iconic Fruito bar, Weis has since grown to be the ice cream fruit experts Australians know and love today. At Weis our products are based on recipes, so the focus is on the subtle blending of real ingredients and ultimately the taste. Our knowledge and expertise in sourcing and working with all different kinds of fruits, premium grade nuts and natural ingredients enables us to create unique combinations and taste experiences. After you’ve eaten a Weis product our aim is to leave you feeling surprised and delighted with the real taste of the wonderful natural ingredients that we use. Above all, we are committed to capturing the true-to-the-source, natural taste of each ingredient we use. You’ll find Weis Bars all around Australia in convenience stores, milk bars and service stations. Our Multipacks, Frozen Yoghurts and Sorbets ranges are stocked by major supermarket chains and independent grocery stores. You can also indulge in a Weis Bar on some international flights departing Australia.
Gluten Free
25% less sugar than the original mango and toasted coconut frozen yoghurt recipe
Made with real Kensington Pride mangoes
Natural colours
Natural flavours
Halal and Kosher certified
